<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"> <channel><title>Ian Barnes</title><description>Random thoughts</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link><atom:link href="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en</language> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:11:21 -0000</pubDate> <lastBuildDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:11:21 -0000</lastBuildDate> <ttl>1440</ttl> <generator>MkDocs RSS plugin - v1.17.2</generator> <image> <url>null</url> <title>Ian Barnes</title><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link> </image> <item> <title>Home</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Home&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Infrequent random writing, sometimes with pictures. A mix of scientific /mathematical curiosities, “creative&#34; pieces, opinions. Might even becontro...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</guid> </item> <item> <title>About</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;About me&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Mugshot&#34; src=&#34;assets/2024-01-19-blue-check-shirt.jpg&#34;&gt;{ width=25% }&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I grew up in Sydney, studied pure mathematics and computer science at theAustra...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Visualisation of periodic surfaces</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Visualisation of periodic surfaces&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here are some images I generated while I was writing my [PhD thesis][thesis].These are all the solutions of simple equations involving trig functions, butare close to and share symmetry and topology with periodic minimal surfaces,which are difficult to calculate and work with.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Foucault&#39;s pendulum</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Foucault&#39;s pendulum&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;I visited the Panthéon yesterday, and saw the original Foucault&#39;s pendulum.Well, sort of. It&#39;s the same location, but it got taken down when the Panthéonbecame a church again for a while, and was then restored, and then the wirebroke and they had to replace it. And at some point the original 28kg bob wasreplaced with one almost twice as heavy. So it&#39;s a bit like the story about theaxe that&#39;s had three new handles and two new heads...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Another periodic surface image</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Another periodic surface image&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a follow-up to &lt;a href=&#34;2020-12-20-visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces.md&#34;&gt;Visualisation of periodicsurfaces&lt;/a&gt;. A while ago I sawthis 3D printed Gyroid model advertised online and couldn&#39;t resist it. Design by&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bathsheba.com/&#34;&gt;Bathsheba Grossman&lt;/a&gt;, printed on demand by&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.shapeways.com/product/QNFAKNW9Z/gyroid&#34;&gt;Shapeways&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Oystercatchers</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Oystercatchers&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A sort of poem, with illustrations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Cloud</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Cloud&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lying on my back&lt;br&gt;Stretching my glutes&lt;br&gt;Looking out the upside-down window&lt;br&gt;Leaves, wind, smears on the glass...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:10:56 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>